data.text:
7/9 Helio Protocol has recently published a Medium article diving deep into the topic of destablecoins! 🗞

Check it out 👇
https://t.co/HrC5WYv8qS

6/9 To give everyone an equal opportunity to farm rewards at a high APY at the start of the farm, we have set a max stake per wallet cap:

100 CAKE for the first 57,600 blocks (aprox 48hrs) after the Syrup Pool is launched, then unlimited CAKE staking afterwards.
5/9 Early $HAY adopters will receive a $HELIO token allocation - more info coming soon ⏳

4/9 Destablecoin vs Stablecoin 🪙

Destablecoins are: 
⚡️ Decentralized
⚡️ Use decentralized assets ($BNB) as collateral + levarage on liquid staked assets
⚡️ $HAY will be redeemable at US $1 worth of crypto

3/9 Destablecoin is a new asset class that is over-collateralized with liquid staked assets.

$HAY is an over-collateralized destablecoin, where 1 $HAY is always redeemable at $1 of cryptocurrency, and over-collateralized by $BNB.
2/9 Developed on the @BNBChain, Helio Protocol is an open-source liquidity protocol for borrowing and earning yield on their native destablecoin $HAY.

data.text:
3/4 The term “stablecoin” or even “algorithmic stablecoin” is generally a misnomer, as all stablecoins, including fiat-backed ones, have the potential to de-peg.

$HAY doesn't use an “algorithm” to regulate its value, but rather through the use of over-collateralized assets. 😉

2/4 Helio protocol is fully decentralized ⚡️

The prefix “de” in “destablecoins” stand for decentralized, and that is to clearly distinguish products such as HAY from other legacy stablecoin products such as BUSD and USDC, which is controlled by a centralized custodian.
